        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary><h3>What is the best way to invest in stocks for beginners?</h3></summary>
          <p>The best approach for beginners is typically investing in broad-market index funds or ETFs (Exchange-Traded Funds) rather than picking individual stocks. This strategy provides instant diversification, lowers risk, and historically outperforms the vast majority of professional active managers.</p>
        </details>

